import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='region', y='total', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of total income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['income_per_capita'] = data['total'] * data['pct']
    avg_income_per_capita = data.groupby('region')['income_per_capita'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='region', y='income_per_capita', data=avg_income_per_capita)
    plt.title('What is the average income per capita in each region?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).agg({'total': 'sum'}).reset_index()
    data_pivot = data_grouped.pivot_table(index='region', columns='group', values='total', fill_value=0)
    data_pivot = data_pivot.div(data_pivot.sum(axis=1), axis=0)
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income groups across different regions?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
